snippet.textDisplay:
It’s really sad that the magic of songs is missing… The old pattern of Habib Wahid’s music used to have a certain magic, but that essence is completely missing in his fusion work. Because of this, for quite a few years Habib hasn’t been able to give his listeners truly good songs.

When Coke Studio Bangla released a fusion track with Habib Wahid, where their main theme is “real magic,” and the song itself was even named Magic , expectations naturally went sky-high. Honestly, I felt disappointed. On top of that, it’s been a long time since foreign languages started being used in the songs, which doesn’t fit well either. Habib’s own part in the song also didn’t land properly.

All in all, the song had no impact. Habib failed, and Coke Studio Bangla is losing its own standard.
